<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-79-0549 </DOCNO><TEXT>GAO examines the implications of current scientific knowledge for policydecisions on acid rain and offers a series of observations on the followingissues involved in the debate: to what extent has it been scientificallydemonstrated that acid rain is resulting in damage to the environment?What are the causes of acid rain and where is it most prevalent? Whatalternatives exist for controlling acid rain and what are their economiceffects?</TEXT></DOC>